#Approach:

Left Rotate Array by K – Reversal Algorithm (Approach)

Sabse pehle k ko normalize kar lo using k = k % n, kyunki agar k > n hoga to extra rotations ka koi fayda nahi.

Ab array ko 3 steps me reverse karna hota hai:

Step 1: Reverse first k elements
Step 2: Reverse remaining n-k elements
Step 3: Reverse whole array

Isse array left rotate ho jata hai by k positions.

Example:
[1 2 3 4 5 6], k = 2

Reverse first k:
[2 1 3 4 5 6]

Reverse remaining:
[2 1 6 5 4 3]

Reverse whole array:
[3 4 5 6 1 2]

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(1) (In-place rotation)

Memory Trick:
Reverse first k + Reverse rest + Reverse whole


#Code:

class Solution {

    private void reverse(int[] nums, int start, int end){
        while(start < end){
            int temp = nums[start];
            nums[start] = nums[end];
            nums[end] = temp;

            start++;
            end--;
        }
    }

    public void rotateArray(int[] nums, int k) {
        int n = nums.length;
        k = k % n;

        reverse(nums, 0, k-1);
        reverse(nums, k, n-1);
        reverse(nums, 0, n-1);
    }
}
